cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.AR 

This paper discusses techniques for compressing and processing sorted lists of integers, which are commonly used in inverted indexes and database systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses data structures and algorithms for processing these compressed lists, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also mentions the use of SIMD instructions, which could fall under cs.CR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.AR (Computer Architecture).
